frameDefinitions: The number of entities that make up the Set changes from an Initial_number to a Final_number.
An Agent or a Cause disperses or scatters Individuals from the Source,a relatively confined space, to a the Goal_area, a broader space.
This frame is concerned with transparent nouns denoting a Piece of a Substance.
This frame has to do with the repetition (and especially the frequency of repetition) of an event.
The LUs in this frame describe the level that a Rate, or the variation in some quantity over a period of time, deviates from the norm.
frameExamples: How has the <t>proliferation</t> of cellular telephones affected your amateur mobile operation? INI INI
She <t>scattered</t> his ashes in the bay.
Kim ate a tiny <t><fex name='Piece'>morsel</fex></t> of cake
China will have to face a high <t>frequency</t> of sand storms in the years to come.
The <t>rapid</t> increase in obesity is a major cause of concern.
listRoleDefinitions: The group of entities, possibly construed as a collective, whose number changes.
The number of entities by which the <fen>Set</fen> increases or decreases.
The number of entities in the <fen>Set</fen> afterwards.
The initial number of entities in the <fen>Set</fen>.
A description that presents the <fen>Set</fen>'s state before the change in the number of entities making it up as an independent predication.
A description that presents the <fen>Set</fen>'s state after  the change in the <fen>Attribute</fen>'s value as an independent predication.
The <fen>Time</fen> is the time-frame in which the change in number occurs.
A location where the <fen>Set</fen> changes in number.
The <fen>Agent</fen> disperses or scatters the <fen>Individuals</fen>.
The <fen>Individuals</fen> are scattered by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
An event or force that causes that <fen>Individuals</fen> to disperse.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Individuals</fen> are dispersed.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the dispersing event happens.
A <fen>Piece</fen> made of a substance.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is what the <fen>Piece</fen> is made of and may describe the type of larger whole from which it came.
This role is used for any (bounded) <fen>Event</fen> whose frequency or iteration is described.
The extent to which the actually observed rate of occurrence of the <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> differs from the expected rate.
The <fen>Interval</fen> is a noun modified by the target word. The target word specifies the frequency of the <fen>Interval</fen> .
The <fen>Time_span</fen> is the length of time of the <fen>Interval</fen>. This role is incorporated by most of the lexical units in this frame.
The number of times per unit of real or scanning time that an <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is encountered.
An entity which the implicit cognizer encounters with the specified frequency.
The frequency feature of the <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> that is under discussion. All the lexical units in this frame incorporate this frame element.
The Time when the Event has a particular frequency.
The <fen>Event</fen> whose <fen>Rate</fen> is being described.
The <fen>Rate</fen> at which something happens during an <fen>Event</fen>.
